    "1: 2:L ← 2 3: 4: 5: 8:w1223458function ExtToeplitz n,m (u, v) floor(log 2 (2n)+1) ▷ Calculate NTT size create u ′ of size L create v ′ of size L for i = 0... m -1 do 6: v ′ [i] ← v[i] for i = 0... n -1 do 9: u ′ [i] ← u[i] 10: v ′ [L -n + 1 + i] = v[m + i] ← conv(u ′, v ′)13: a = max{1, log 22(m -2 exp(1)) -log 2 (t -2 exp(1)) log 2 (2 exp(1)) -log 2 (2 exp(1) -1)}, 1: 3:do 4:134function ExtVonNeumann(b) 2: out = []for i = 0... ⌊len(b)/2⌋ -1 if b[2i] ̸ = b[2i + 1] The NTT can be seen as a generalisation of the FFT to finite fields, allowing to perform fast convolutions on integer sequences.",
